		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I found more information in some japanese forum.
<br />
<br />Actually, people that did pre-order the DVD received a rom kit+board.. They had to solder back the cartridge together.  
<br />
<br />Here a picture of the dvd set + box:
<br /><a href="http://www.gizmodo.jp/img/ggxms080128_1.jpg" class="postlink">http://www.gizmodo.jp/img/ggxms080128_1.jpg</a>
<br />
<br />It doesn't use any mapper, only the 2 chips.  Here a picture of the board:
<br /><a href="http://www.gizmodo.jp/img/ggxms080128_3.jpg" class="postlink">http://www.gizmodo.jp/img/ggxms080128_3.jpg</a>
<br />
<br />Its a custom made board for that project. 
<br />
<br />Here's a picture of the chips+soldering:
<br /><a href="http://www.gizmodo.jp/img/ggxms080128_2.jpg" class="postlink">http://www.gizmodo.jp/img/ggxms080128_2.jpg</a>
