	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Banshaku</b> [ Sun Aug 17, 2008 6:39 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I received today the answer regarding the DVD-BOX set and the meaning of "source included". Here's the answer (in japanese):
<br />
<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">お問い合わせありがとう<br />ございます。<br /><br />DVD-BOXについているCD-ROMにはMr.SPLASH!の6502のアセンブラのソースコード<br />が全部入っています。<br />nesasnmでコンパイルできます。<br /><br />ただし<br />CD-ROMを作ったときの我々のミスで、ソースファイルのディレクトリ構造が壊れ<br />ているので<br />そのままではコンパイルできません。<br />もし、DVD購入後に質問があれば、もう一度お問い合わせください。<br /><br />Project F<br />POLYGON INUKAI<br /></div>
<br />
<br />Basically, what they say is that the CD-ROM contains the source in 6502 and they can be compiled with nesasm.  But, when they produced the CD, there was a mistake in the directory structure so some file are broken/missing.  If you do buy the DVD-BOX, you can ask the files to them.
<br />
<br />It's interesting to see that they used nesasm for their project. By seeing the board they used, since it requires no mapper, they I guess nesasm must be enough for the task.
<br />
<br />So this mean, if you get the DVD-BOX set and request the source code, you could have "Mr. Splash!" running in an emulator.  I don't know how much "value" it would have but that's good to know.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


